result.execSummary:
The defendant Keith J Griffin was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-Heroin (<=3g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(d)1.
  • Possess w/Intent-Cocaine (>1-5g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(cm)1r.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Certification of PLEA & SENTENCING transcript commencing 08-21-2015 received and filed. (44 Pages.)  CH
Per order of the Presiding Judge, Felony Division, this request/motion is hereby assigned to the Hon. Daniel L. Konkol, Br. 44, for review. mag
Defendant's pro se request for sentence credit.

Defendant Keith J Griffin in court with attorney Maayan Silver.  Defendant Keith J Griffin in custody.  Anthony E. White appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

AS TO COUNT 1:
Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum  and Elements/Jury Instructions, received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to amended complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information.

Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered Count #1 Modifier dismissed.

AS TO COUNT 2:
Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum  and Elements/Jury Instructions, received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information.

Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered Count #2 Modifier dismissed.

AS TO COUNT 3:
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered Count #3 with Modifier dismissed and read-in for the purposes of sentencing.  

Sentencing proceeds.  No corrections made to the PSI report.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by counsel and defendant.  

COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms, he must provide a DNA sample, if this conviction is reversed, set aside or vacated you may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if you meet conditions under the statute and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

Count 1:  COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE - 3 years with zero (0) days credit; INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT - 1 year, 6 months; EXTENDED SUPERVISION - 1 year, 6 months - concurrent to the revocation; pay mandatory costs, assessments  and surcharges by the end of the sentence or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant and subject to other collection.

Count 2:  COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE - 3 years; INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT - 1 year, 6 months; EXTENDED SUPERVISION - 1 year, 6 months - concurrent to Count 1; mandatory costs, assessments and surcharges waived by the Court.

Court finds defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  1) no violations of criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) pay any monetary amounts ordered but not paid while in the institution; 3) AODA, programs or treatment as recommended; 4) mental health trama counseling, programs or treatment as recommended; programs or treatment as recommended; 5) do not use or possess illegally controlled substances; 6) random screening; 7) seek and maintain employment. 

COURT ORDERS:
- DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of prison funds;
- defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence, Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief, Pretrial Incarceration Credit and Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgment received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.

Defendant Keith J Griffin in court with attorney Maayan Silver.  Defendant Keith J Griffin in custody.  Dennis Patrick Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Original Information filed 6/10/2015.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty.  Defense counsel requests a plea date.  Defense will file any motions within 2 weeks.  Court advised parties that as of August 3, 2015, this case will be reassigned to Judge Daniel Konkol, Branch 44 in Room 316 of the Safety Bldg.  Case adjourned for plea and sentencing on 8/3/2015 at 8:30 am, branch 44.  aw  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 3, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Court took judicial notice of certified documents regarding case #04CF2375 that are attached to the complaint.  Sworn for the state:Adam Schweitzer-West Allis Police Department Officer.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading.  Case is adjourned to Branch 03.

Defendant Keith J Griffin in court with attorney Maayan Silver.  Defendant Keith J Griffin in custody.  Nathaniel Adamson for Antonella Aleman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
State files an AMENDED CRIMINAL COMPLAINT.  COUNT 1:POSSESSION WITH INTENT TO DELIVER CONTROLLED SUBSTANCE (HEROIN) (3 GRAMS OR LESS), SECOND AND SUBSEQUENT OFFENSE contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 961.41(1m)(d)1, 939.50(3)(f), 961.48(1)(b), a Class F Felony.  COUNT 2:POSSESSION WITH INTENT TO DELIVER COCAINE (>1-5G), SECOND AND SUBSEQUENT OFFENSE contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 961.41(1m)(cm)1r, 939.50(3)(f), 961.48(1)(b), a Class F Felony.  COUNT 3:POSSESSION OF NARCOTIC DRUGS, SECOND AND SUBSEQUENT OFFENSE contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 961.41(3g)(am), 939.50(3)(i), 961.48(1)(b), a Class F Felony.  
Defense motion to dismiss the AMENDED criminal complaint is denied by the Court.  
Defendant given a copy of the complaint.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  Arraignment scheduled for June 23, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Original warrant not in court file.  Court ordered bench warrant withdrawn.  Recall issued.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision.  DEFENDANT to be monitored by drug testing.  No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Keith J Griffin in court with attorney Darryl E. Smith.  Defendant Keith J Griffin in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Fiorenza, Branch 03.  State moves to amend charging portion of criminal complaint as to Count 2 removing Selection 2 and adding cocaine.  Defense does not object.  Court grants motion to amend.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 10, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant Keith J Griffin not in court.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
